Set 27 
Collection “movies“ which contains the documents given as below(Perform on Mongo Terminal)  
{  
name: “Movie1”,  
type: “action”,  
budget:1000000  
producer:{  
name: “producer1”,  
address:”PUNE”  
}  
}  
i. Find the name of the movie having budget greater than 1,00,000.  
ii. Find the name of producer who lives in Pune  
iii. Update the type of movie “action” to “horror”  
iv. Find all the documents produced by name “producer1” with their address  




use moviedb

db.createCollection("movies")

db.movies.insertOne({
name:"Movie1",
type:"action",
budget:1000000,
producer:{
name:"producer1",
address:"PUNE"
}
})

// 1. Find movie names having budget greater than 100000

db.movies.find(
{
budget:{$gt:100000}
},
{
name:1,
_id:0
}
)

// 2. Find producer names living in Pune

db.movies.find(
{
"producer.address":"PUNE"
},
{
"producer.name":1,
_id:0
}
)

// 3. Update movie type from action to horror

db.movies.updateMany(
{
type:"action"
},
{
$set:{type:"horror"}
}
)

// 4. Find documents produced by producer1

db.movies.find(
{
"producer.name":"producer1"
}
)
